text.tspan: both the client (View) and the server (VirtualView)
have access to one object of this kind. When one
machine invokes the broadcast method, the given
EventData object gets serialized into a JSON string
and sent over the network to the other machine
(through a Connection object not shown for brevity).
The NetworkEventTransceiver on the other end
deserializes the JSON string in the corresponding
EventData object and invokes the handle method
on all the event listeners registered for that kind
